public class SearchFlowPanel<C extends Serializable,B extends Serializable>
extends ServicePanelWithBack

ServicePanel that manages a simple UI flow of a query. This UI flow consists of:

  • A screen that allows the user to define criteria for the query and execute it.
  • A screen that shows the results and allows the user to select one (or more) items or go back to the previous screen.
    • Anyone using this, should provide the following CallbackActions.
  • back action (optionally).
  • query action (should put the results in this panel's definition).
  • selected item(s) action (should retrieve the selected item(s) from this panel's definition and do something with it.
  • delete, update, save action (should retrieve the item to perform the operation on from the beanModel of this panel's definition.

    Hook intended to be overridden by the user if he chooses to set readBeforeEdit to true in the SearchFlowPanelDef. TODO: If an exception is caught here, there is no way to register the message in a feedback panel that is ajax updated.

    Returns:

    copyBean

    protected B copyBean(B bean)
    Hook intended to be overridden by the user. This is useful if when updating a B instance there is a chance that the update will be aborted after submitting the update form. This could happen, for example, if a validation message is shown and the user decides to go back instead of correcting the error and submitting the update form again. If readBeforeEdit is true, this is not used, as instead of deep copying, a new instance is created from the persistence layer, which has the same effect.

    Parameters:
    bean - instance to copy.
    Returns:
    Returns a copy of B.
